James Trick "Jimmy" Jose (1881 – 1963) was a Cornish rugby union player born in Falmouth who played for both Falmouth RFC and Devonport Albion (now Plymouth Albion). Jose gained 20 caps for Cornwall between 1904-11 and was a member of the famous 1908 County Championship winning side who beat Durham 17-3 at Redruth. 
Also on 26 October 1908 playing for Cornwall who were representing Great Britain he competed in the 1908 Summer Olympics at White City Stadium, London losing to Australia in the final.
